The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 February is 307,884 (35,485.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 January, there were 189 new confirmed cases (21.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 154 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (35 extra cases).
